      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 314: The foreground/background counter can become negative if lifecycle callbacks are unbalanced, for example with unusual activity launch flows, multi-window behavior, or an Activity stopped after state restoration edge cases. A negative value prevents the next foreground transition from satisfying `startedActivities \u003d\u003d 1`, so the connectivity refresh may stop firing until process restart. Clamp the counter when stopping. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\nstartedActivities \u003d (startedActivities - 1).coerceAtLeast(0)\nif (startedActivities \u003d\u003d 0) {\n    backgroundTimestamp \u003d android.os.SystemClock.elapsedRealtime()\n}\n```",
