      "message": "[🟡 Suggestion] Line 51: Changing the call-push gate from delivered `priority` to `originalPriority` means pushes that FCM downgraded to normal priority will still trigger the expensive connectivity refresh path. That weakens the battery-drain mitigation described below and may reintroduce excessive wakeups when FCM deprioritizes traffic. If the intent is to refresh only for pushes actually delivered as high priority, keep the delivered priority check; if original priority is intentionally required, update the battery-drain rationale and consider adding an additional throttle. Suggested fix:\n```suggestion\n                \u0026\u0026 remoteMessage.priority \u003d\u003d RemoteMessage.PRIORITY_HIGH\n```",
